## Sample Input for `sample-data.json`

Use this exact starting dataset:

[
	{"name": "Samsung Galaxy S23", "price": 799.99},
	{"name": "SAMSUNG   GALAXY S23!!!", "price": 749.99},
	{"name": "סמסונ גלקסי s23", "price": 770.00},
	{"name": "iPhone 15 Pro", "price": 1099.00},
	{"name": "iPhone 15 Pro", "price": 999.99},
	{"name": "Google Pixel 8", "price": 799.00},
	{"name": "google pixel 8", "price": 750.00},
	{"name": "  iPad Air  ", "price": 620.00},
	{"name": "iPad Air", "price": 599.00}
]

Expected behavior:
- English Samsung variants merge to one with 749.99.
- Hebrew Samsung remains separate in this lean version unless mapped explicitly.
- iPhone merges to 999.99.
- Pixel merges to 750.00.
- iPad merges to 599.00.

